  '<h2 id="csp">CSP and inline content</h2>',

  '<h3>b.middleware.cspNonce() <a class="anchor" href="#csp-nonce">#</a></h3>',
  '<p>Generates a fresh 16-byte random base64-url nonce per response and exposes it on <code>res.locals.cspNonce</code>. The framework default CSP is intentionally strict — no <code>\'unsafe-inline\'</code>. Apps that need an inline script or style for a single element use the nonce on that element; the response header carries <code>nonce-XYZ</code>. Nonces expire with the response so an attacker can\'t cache one to inject later.</p>',
